The paper deals with the visualization of hierarchically structured data over time, which is a topic that falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of streamgraphs, which are a type of graph visualization commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data visualization (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions the handling of topological changes, which is a topic in database management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper proposes a new visual metaphor, which could potentially fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
